\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/figure><!-- .featured-image -->\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"entry-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/2024\/12\/21\/hong-kong-govt-has-no-business-in-show-business-especially-when-times-are-tight\/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Hong Kong gov&#8217;t has no business in show\u00a0business &#8211; especially when times are tight<\/a><\/h3>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"newspack-post-subtitle newspack-post-subtitle--in-homepage-block\">\n\t\t\t\t\t&#8220;The government&#8217;s role in fostering mega events should be confined to ensuring there are suitable venues for them,&#8221; writes Tim Hamlett. &#8220;The relevant industries will produce a steady flow of&#8230; opportunities to buy expensive items or to watch Lionel Messi watch a football match.&#8221;\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"byline\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"author-prefix\">by<\/span> <span class=\"author vcard\"><a class=\"url fn n\" href=\"https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/author\/timhamlett\/\">Tim Hamlett<\/a><\/span>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span><!-- .author-name -->\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div><!-- .entry-wrapper -->\n\t<\/article>\n\n\t\t"},{"html":"\n\t<article data-post-id=\"499125\"\n\t\tclass=\"tag-airport-authority-hong-kong tag-economy tag-hong-kong-international-airport category-business category-comments-analysis category-politics-protest category-travel type-of-work-opinion type-post post-has-image\"\n\t\t\t\t>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/2024\/12\/15\/hong-kongs-third-runway-game-changer-or-hk140-billion-white-elephant\/\" rel=\"bookmark\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Tim-airport-runway.jpg\" class=\"attachment-newspack-article-block-uncropped size-newspack-article-block-uncropped wp-post-image\" alt=\"Hong Kong&#8217;s third runway: Game-changer or HK$140 billion white elephant?\" data-hero-candidate=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Tim-airport-runway.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Tim-airport-runway-1050x591.jpg 1050w, https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Tim-airport-runway-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Tim-airport-runway-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Tim-airport-runway-400x225.jpg 400w, https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Tim-airport-runway-706x397.jpg 706w, https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Tim-airport-runway-800x450.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 34.9rem) calc(100vw - 2rem), (max-width: 53rem) calc(8 * (100vw \/ 12)), (min-width: 53rem) calc(6 * (100vw \/ 12)), 100vw\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/figure><!-- .featured-image -->\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"entry-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https:\/\/hongkongfp.com\/2024\/12\/15\/hong-kongs-third-runway-game-changer-or-hk140-billion-white-elephant\/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Hong Kong&#8217;s third runway: Game-changer or HK$140 billion white elephant?<\/a><\/h3>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"newspack-post-subtitle newspack-post-subtitle--in-homepage-block\">\n\t\t\t\t\t&#8220;If you are getting a million tourists a year, and your airport can handle two million, then upgrading it to a capacity of three million is not going to make the slightest difference,&#8221; writes Tim Hamlett. &#8220;People are not going to visit especially to see the new airport. It is a means to an end.&#8221;\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"byline\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"au